&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle4&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://bluevisual.tv/images/honeyglue-04.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/label&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;Motion path of the bee in the first scene&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; name=&#34;lightbox-toggle4&#34; id=&#34;lightbox-toggle4&#34; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;lightbox&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&#34;lightbox-toggle4&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://bluevisual.tv/images/honeyglue-04.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;Motion path of the bee in the first scene&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;VFX was only half the project. I was also contracted to do storybook animations for certain narrative portions of the film. I was provided with Photoshop assets from an illustrator who drew them. My job was to take the layers/characters and animate them. I decided to go beyond the 2D realm of a book and try a sort of 3D parallaxing style. The clients enjoyed it so I went through with it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;project-image&#34; oncontextmenu=&#34;return false;&#34;&gt;
